[
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"413824\">@Gary Guo</span> <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"546447\">@Benno Lossin</span>  I just want to follow up it by pointing out seems to me that explictly <code>.deref()</code> can get around the lint, e.g. <code>dma_read!(dma[0].derefer.deref().field)</code>.</p>",
        "id": 571998329,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1770235259
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>oh yeah you're right</p>",
        "id": 571998489,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1770235307
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but we can change the macro to only allow idents in the <code>fields</code> part</p>",
        "id": 571998517,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1770235319
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>then the <code>()</code> will not work</p>",
        "id": 571998538,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1770235324
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think it's already doing ident list today?</p>",
        "id": 571998577,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1770235339
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>no not the fields for the projections, that uses <code>tt</code></p>",
        "id": 571998600,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1770235349
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh yes I misread</p>",
        "id": 571998670,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1770235369
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>so the two things we need to do:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>make the lint <code>forbid</code></li>\n<li>only allow idents and dots in the project part</li>\n</ol>",
        "id": 571998770,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1770235400
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm reworking the macro anyway, so I'll make sure to forbid that</p>",
        "id": 571998776,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1770235402
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>good catch <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"411647\">@Boqun Feng</span> !</p>",
        "id": 571998797,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1770235410
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"413824\">Gary Guo</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/Soundness.20of.20.60dma_read!.28.29.60/near/571998776\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I'm reworking the macro anyway, so I'll make sure to forbid that</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>one of the arms was unnecessary and could be folded into the other</p>",
        "id": 571998835,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1770235424
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(Nova needs to do indexing I think, so just ident won't work)</p>",
        "id": 571998846,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1770235426
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I wonder whether we can just <code>offset_of!()</code> instead of <code>addr_of!()</code> here, and put the <code>offset_of!()</code> into a <code>const</code></p>",
        "id": 571998888,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1770235439
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>does that also pose the same issue with <code>Index</code>?</p>",
        "id": 571998894,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1770235442
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>with <code>offset_of!</code> you need to supply the starting type</p>",
        "id": 571998936,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1770235460
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>which we don't have</p>",
        "id": 571998939,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1770235463
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Index is also catched by dangerous implicit autoref lint it seems</p>",
        "id": 571999507,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1770235664
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"546447\">Benno Lossin</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/Soundness.20of.20.60dma_read!.28.29.60/near/571998517\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>but we can change the macro to only allow idents in the <code>fields</code> part</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>we also should support <code>0</code>, <code>1</code>, <code>2</code> .. in the <code>fields</code>, so it's <code>ident</code> plus <code>literal</code>?</p>",
        "id": 572015821,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1770241444
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Update from the Rust side, while looking into the lint, I discovered that it doesnt trigger on std's <code>Box</code>, since that uses a special <code>Deref</code> implementation. Then many people chimed in and said that depending on a lint for soundness is not a good idea: <a href=\"https://rust-lang.zulipchat.com/#narrow/channel/213817-t-lang/topic/dangerous_implicit_autorefs.20and.20Box/with/572317154\">https://rust-lang.zulipchat.com/#narrow/channel/213817-t-lang/topic/dangerous_implicit_autorefs.20and.20Box/with/572317154</a></p>",
        "id": 572317334,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1770366326
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>so we probably still need field projections either as suggested in the thread using a derive macro, or with a different hack</p>",
        "id": 572317475,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1770366372
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>grr type inference plz be stronger</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">std</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">mem</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">MaybeUninit</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">std</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">marker</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">PhantomData</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">field</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">OffsetIn</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">offset</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">usize</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">_in</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">PhantomData</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">OffsetIn</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">create</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">offset</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">_in</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">PhantomData</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">get_uninit</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">MaybeUninit</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">MaybeUninit</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">uninit</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">get_offset_for</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_t</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">T</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">usize</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">offset</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">main</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">abc</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">field</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">10</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">offset</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">offset_in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">OffsetIn</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">create</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">dummy</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">offset_in</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">get_uninit</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">dummy</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_mut_ptr</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">offset</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">raw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">field</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">offset_in</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">offset</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"n\">dummy</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_mut_ptr</span><span class=\"p\">().</span><span class=\"n\">offset_from</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">offset</span><span class=\"p\">)};</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">offset_in</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">offset</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">offset</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">get_offset_for</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">abc</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Text only\"><pre><span></span><code>error[E0282]: type annotations needed for `OffsetIn&lt;_&gt;`\n  --&gt; src/main.rs:35:13\n   |\n35 |         let mut offset_in = OffsetIn::create();\n   |             ^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n...\n38 |         let offset = unsafe { &amp;raw mut (*ptr).field };\n   |                                        ------ type must be known at this point\n   |\nhelp: consider giving `offset_in` an explicit type, where the placeholders `_` are specified\n   |\n35 |         let mut offset_in: OffsetIn&lt;T&gt; = OffsetIn::create();\n   |                          +++++++++++++\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 572321646,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1770367703
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Here I solved it:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&amp;mode=debug&amp;edition=2024&amp;gist=2d4c2a76b972c2ecd66f91928db853d0\">https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&amp;mode=debug&amp;edition=2024&amp;gist=2d4c2a76b972c2ecd66f91928db853d0</a></p>",
